The paper focuses on biometric template protection, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves transforming biometric feature vectors into discrete hashed codes, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) fields. The paper also discusses the robustness and accuracy of the proposed method, which are topics commonly studied in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) subfields.
